quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  4,128,"And if a woman fears disloyalty or disregard from her husband, then no sin is committed by them if they <span class=""h"">reform<sup foot_note=""79891"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">what is between themselves{2} </span>, for reconciliation is better. Yet stinginess has been brought to the<i class=""s"">(inner) </i>selves. But if you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>excel in doing good and become mindful<i class=""s"">(of God) </i>—indeed, Allah has always been All-Aware of what you do.",footnotes:2:Literally, ‘if they reconcile a reconciliation’.
  4,129,"Furthermore, you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>will not be able to be equitable between the women{1}no matter how keen you are, so do not be so biased as to leave her suspended. Rather, if you reform and become mindful<i class=""s"">(of God) </i>—indeed, Allah has always been Oft-Forgiving, Bestowing of mercy.",footnotes:1:Wives.
  4,130,"Yet if they both separate, Allah will enrich each from His vast means{1}, for Allah has always been All-Embracing, All-Wise.",footnotes:1:Literally ‘embracement’.
  4,131,"And to Allah belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is in the earth. And very truly We have admonished those who were brought the Scripture before you, as well as yourselves, “Be mindful of Allah{1}. But if you deny—then to Allah belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is in the earth, and Allah has always been Self-Sufficient, Praiseworthy.”",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from 1st person to 3rd person.
  4,132,"And to Allah belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is in the earth. And sufficient is Allah as a Trustee."
  4,133,"If He wills, He can do away with you, O mankind, and bring others. For Allah has always been All-Able to do that."
  4,134,"Whoever wants the recompense of the Earlier<i class=""s"">(Life) </i>—with Allah is the recompense of the Earlier<i class=""s"">(Life) </i>and the Hereafter. And Allah has always been All-Hearing, All-Seeing."
